ENTRY            A0735   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0735001   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 10         26
TITLE      Decay spectroscopy of suburanium isotopes following
           projectile fragmentation of 238U at 1 GeV/u
AUTHOR     (Z.Liu, J.Kurcewicz, P.J.Woods, C.Mazzocchic,
           F.Attallah, E.Badurac, C.N.Davids, T.Davinson,
           J.Doering, H.Geissel, M.Gorska, R.Grzywacz,
           M.Hellstroem, Z.Janas, M.Karny, A.Korgul, I.Mukha,
           M.Pfuetzner, C.Plettner, A.Robinson, E.Roeckl,
           K.Rykaczewski, K.Schmidt, D.Seweryniak, H.Weick)
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/A,543,591,2005)
INSTITUTE  (2UK EDG,3POLWWA,2GERGSI,1USAANL,1USAORL)
FACILITY   (SYNCH,2GERGSI) The heavy-ion synchrotron SIS with
            fragment separator (FRS).
SAMPLE     A 1 g/cm2 beryllium target located at the entrance of
           the FRS. To maximize the fraction of fully stripped
           ions, a niobium foil of 221 mg/cm2 was placed behind
           the production target.
DETECTOR   (SPEC)
METHOD     (EXTB) The beam was delivered in spills lasting
           6 seconds with a repetition period of 10-18 seconds.
           The beam current was 1.E+7-5.E+8 ions/spill.
           (BCINT) The number of incoming projectiles was measured
           by a secondary electron transmission monitor (SEETRAM).
           Inverse geometry.
ADD-RES    (DECAY) Decay-data for observed products.
HISTORY    (20051031C)
           (20260205U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              26
COMMON               1          3
EN
GEV
       238.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           33
SUBENT        A0735002   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                  3          9
REACTION   (4-BE-9(92-U-238,X)ELEM/MASS,,SIG,,REL)
           Yield per day at beam current of 1.E+7 particle per
           second.
           *By authors*. The dips at 219Pa (T1/2=53 ns),
           218Th (T1/2=109 ns) and 217Ac (T1/2=69 ns) are due
           to the fact that their half-lives are shorter than
           their time of flight from target to detector.
STATUS     (CURVE,,Z.Liu+,J,NIM/A,543,591,2005) Fig.6
HISTORY    (20260205U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB               9
COMMON               1          3
ERR-DIG
PER-CENT
        12.
ENDCOMMON            3
